race.comment: MILES OF GLORY (6) resumed at Newcastle and was beating a whisker after stalking the speed. Jumps from an inside gate today and is sure to have come on. Placed to advantage and has decent claims. FLAXLANDS (8) debuts for the Waller yard and has been well-trialled. Placed the latest at Rosehill and maps for a soft run. The betting will be key. DEEP AFFECTION (7) has raced at Listed and Group level and looked a run short beaten 1.4L at Canberra first up. She has an inside barrier and races forward. Tackling a deeper field this time but she is capable of another big run. LETHAL LOVE (12) resumed in the same race and finished a whisker behind the above. Came hard from a long way back and there was plenty of merit in the effort. She can go on with it.
